This paper deals with the task of argument quality ranking, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of neural methods, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The task of ranking arguments also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place the paper in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the analysis of quality dimensions, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the construction and analysis of a large-scale dataset, which could place it in cs.CY (Computers and Society).
